comment: Speights (LAC) makes incidental contact with Hill (UTA) that does not affect his SQBR.
Rivers (LAC) does not step out of bounds.
Mbah a Moute (LAC) makes incidental contact with Johnson (UTA) that does not affect his FOM.
Favors (UTA) firms up his position and sets the screen on Rivers (LAC).
Redick (LAC) makes incidental contact with Hill (UTA) that does not affect his FOM.
Jordan (LAC) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Hayward (UTA) that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Ingles (UTA) makes incidental contact with Paul (LAC) that does not affect his SQBR.
Johnson (UTA) legally defends Redick (LAC) on the pass.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of UTA possession is confirmed.
Paul (LAC) and Ingles (UTA) briefly engage and separate during the inbound.
Favors (UTA) sets the screen on Rivers (LAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Jordan (LAC) legally contests Hayward's (UTA) jump shot attempt.
Rivers (LAC) and Favors (UTA) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Paul (LAC) makes contact with the ball when it is outside of the cylinder.
Hill (UTA) legally contests Paul's (LAC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Jordan (LAC) and Favors (UTA) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Favors (UTA) makes contact to the body of Jordan (LAC) that affects his putback attempt.
Johnson (UTA) makes incidental contact with Jordan (LAC) that does not affect his ability to defend the play.
Jordan (LAC) legally contests Johnson's (LAC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Hayward (UTA) dislodges Rivers (LAC) and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Redick (LAC) and Hill (UTA) briefly engage and separate during the loose ball.
Ingles (UTA) commits a take foul on Paul (LAC).
